<blockquote class="wp-block-quote is-style-default" style="font-size:26px"><p><em><strong>The call for the protest was given by a social media influencer Vikas Fhatak, alias ‘Hindustani Bhau’, who allegedly makes abusive videos on social media.</strong></em></p></blockquote>



<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="569" src="https://abhishek-tiwaari.github.io/ViralNewsBuzz/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/IMG-20220131-WA0061-1024x569.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-11" srcset="https://abhishek-tiwaari.github.io/ViralNewsBuzz/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/IMG-20220131-WA0061-1024x569.jpg 1024w, https://abhishek-tiwaari.github.io/ViralNewsBuzz/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/IMG-20220131-WA0061-300x167.jpg 300w, https://abhishek-tiwaari.github.io/ViralNewsBuzz/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/IMG-20220131-WA0061-768x427.jpg 768w, https://abhishek-tiwaari.github.io/ViralNewsBuzz/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/IMG-20220131-WA0061.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption><strong>While protests at Jalgaon and Aurangabad remained peaceful, at Mumbai and Nagpur, local police had to resort to lathi-charge to&nbsp;disperse the mob of students, most of whom were minors.</strong></figcaption></figure></div>



<p style="font-size:22px">The Maharashtra state board of secondary and higher secondary education announced that offline exams would be held as per schedule in the state, amidst strict covid protocols. Thousands of students are staging protests against the Maharashtra government’s decision to conduct Class 10, 12 board exams in offline mode. While protests at Jalgaon and Aurangabad remained peaceful, it turned violent in Mumbai and Nagpur, with some students damaging private and police vehicles by pelting stones and blocking roads.</p>



