<p style="font-size:22px">Several hundred students protested on Monday near the residence of Maharashtra school education minister Varsha Gaikwad in Mumbai demanding that offline exams for classes X to XII be cancelled amid the coronavirus pandemic.</p>



<p style="font-size:22px">Meanwhile, Gaikwad has said, &#8220;We&#8217;ve been continuously discussing students&#8217; health &amp; safety. I told students to have discussions with me; I&#8217;ll decide further. But we also have to keep in mind the two-year loss in school students&#8217; education.&#8221;</p>



